  "texts": [
    "Specifically, in constructing the classification framework, and selecting key studies, the authors' research background, academic preferences, and understanding of the field's major trends may have subtly affected the final selection of literature.",
    "Second, the division of AIGC's three application technology areas and ITS's four subsystems into 12 application scenarios may lead to insufficient coverage of certain subfields in the literature.",
    "Although efforts were made to address this issue by expanding the scope of keywords, the comprehensiveness and persuasiveness of the review may still be impacted.",
    "Third, if the review overly relies on theoretical research and lacks a thorough analysis of real-world applications or experimental data, the practical implications of the conclusions may be insufficient.",
    "While some practical cases have been included, the integration of theory and practice remains inadequate, especially in terms of discussing technical challenges, economic costs, and social impacts in real-world deployments."
